name: Bromohydrin pyrophosphate
7.1-Drug Indication: ["Investigated for use/treatment in hepatitis (viral, C), leukemia (myeloid), and lymphoma (non-hodgkin's)."]
8.1-Pharmacodynamics: ['IPH 1101 potentiates the direct cytotoxic activity of V9V2 T cells against a large number of tumor cell lines and also triggers the synthesis of pro-inflammatory cytokines - thus inducing the recruitment of other cell effectors and facilitating implementation of an adaptive response.']
